HEADWORD: Enation
<hw>E*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any unusual outgrowth from the surface of a thing, as of a petal;
also, the capacity or act of producing such an outgrowth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

